    • Method Detail

      • startStream

        public boolean startStream()
        This method sends a request to the headset to START the EEG raw data acquisition process and enables Bluetooth Low Energy notification to receive the raw data.

        Note: calling this method will start the raw EEG data acquisition process on the headset which will consume battery life. Please consider calling stopStream() when EEG raw data are no longer needed.

        Specified by:
        startStream in interface IStreamable
        Returns:
        true if request has been sent correctly false on immediate error

      • stopStream

        public boolean stopStream()
        This method sends a request to the headset to STOP the EEG raw data acquisition process, therefore disabling the Bluetooth Low Energy notification and cleaning reference to previously registered listener.

        Calling this method will preserve battery life by halting the raw EEG data acquisition process on the headset.

        Specified by:
        stopStream in interface IStreamable
        Returns:
        true upon correct EEG disability request, false on immediate error

      • startLowEnergyScan

        public android.bluetooth.BluetoothDevice startLowEnergyScan(boolean filterOnDeviceService,
                                                            boolean filterOnDeviceName)
        Start bluetooth low energy scanner in order to find BLE device that matches the specific filters.

        Note: This method will consume your mobile/tablet battery. Please consider calling stopLowEnergyScan() when scanning is no longer needed.

        Parameters:
        filterOnDeviceService -
        filterOnDeviceName -
        Returns:
        Each found device that matches the specified filters
